Police in Oregon are enlisting the help of the public to identify a mystery motorcyclist who saved the day after Edward West, 59, allegedly threatened two teens with a handgun .
The boys were crossing Center Street when a stranger on a green motorcycle swooped in and used his helmet to knock the gun out of the man's hands, allowing the teens to escape .
West, 59 was arrested and charged with menacing, harassment, assault, and unlawful use of a weapon .